			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Sodium hydroxide (NaOH), also known as caustic soda or lye, is a corrosive white crystalline solid. It readily absorbs moisture until it dissolves and is the most widely used industrial alkali. It is used in the manufacture of various medicines and pharmaceutical products, including aspirin, anticoagulants, and cholesterol-reducing medications. It is also used in fuel cell production. Sodium hydroxide is an ionic crystal composed of Na+ cations and OH- anions. It is characterized by its colorless appearance, lack of odor, and high deliquescence.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氢氧化钠（NaOH）又称烧碱或碱液，是一种腐蚀性白色结晶固体。它很容易吸收水分直至溶解，是应用最广泛的工业碱。它可用于制造各种药物和医药产品，包括阿司匹林、抗凝血剂和降低胆固醇的药物。它还用于燃料电池的生产。氢氧化钠是一种离子晶体，由 Na+ 阳离子和 OH- 阴离子组成。其特点是外观无色、无味、潮解度高。</common:generalComment>
